This paper deals with the design of a UAV-enabled radio access network for communication with ground users. The paper proposes algorithms for joint UAV trajectory and communication resource allocation design, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also considers the optimization of UAV flight duration and mission completion time, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The paper utilizes iterative algorithms and block coordinate descent techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also deals with trajectory design, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper considers multi-mode communication, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
